lead_paragraph: The Green Bay Packers designated defensive tackle Corey Williams as their franchise player, preventing him from becoming an unrestricted free agent. Green Bay also cut tight end Bubba Franks after eight seasons. A first-round draft choice in 2000, Franks had 256 catches for 2,300 yards, and 32 touchdowns.
